accessibility.text: AWS Lambda is a serverless compute platform launched by Amazon Web Services in April of 2014.
It was the first service that provided this model of hosting and now has spawned a whole industry of functions as a service:
Vercel, Netlify, Heroku (based on AWS Lambda),
Google Cloud Functions, and Azure Functions (alternatives)
Has integration with other AWS services such as DynamoDB and S3 storage buckets.
